Footnotes:
1. Data for in situ breast cancers are listed separately and are not included in the "All Invasive Cancer Sites Combined" or
"Male and Female Breast" cancer categories.
Caveats:
1. Statistics are suppressed to protect personal privacy, for the following conditions: <ol><li> Data are suppressed if the

figures represent fewer than 16 cases for the specific category in the table cell.
  • Counts and rates are suppressed for
cells at the Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA) level for the race categories "American Indian or Alaska Native" or "Asian

or Pacific Islander" when the specific category's population for rate calculations is less than 50,000 persons.
  • Data
are suppressed at the state and MSA level for certain race and ethnicity groups: <ul><li> American Indian or Alaska Native data

are suppressed at the state and MSA level for residents of Illinois, Kansas, New Jersey, and New York;
  • Asian or

Pacific Islander data are suppressed at the state and MSA level for residents of Illinois, and Kansas;
  • Race by
ethnicity data are suppressed for state specific statistics for residents of Kansas, Illinois, and Massachusetts.
States decide whether to suppress data for specific race and ethnicity categories. The suppression criteria may vary
in previous releases of these data More information: http://wonder.cdc.gov/wonder/help/cancer-v2019.html#Confidentiality.
2. 'Not Applicable' is displayed for all data values when sex-specific cancers are combined with the wrong sex. More
information: http://wonder.cdc.gov/wonder/help/cancer-v2019.html#Genital Cancers List.
3. 'Missing' is displayed for a combination of states/territories/MSAs and years that did not meet the United States Cancer
Statistics (USCS) publication standard or did not allow permission for their data to be used.
4. The "Show Totals" checkbox is disabled when data are grouped by Cancer Sites or by Childhood Cancer, because aggregate
values are displayed in the table. Also be aware that charts and maps containing both aggregate and detail data could be
misleading.
5. Age-adjusted rates are not available when results are grouped by age.
6. These states are missing data for the indicated year: Mississippi 1999-2002; Nevada 2018-2019; South Dakota 1999-2000.
7. Data are from selected statewide and metropolitan area cancer registries that meet data quality criteria. Incidence data
shown for the United States are diagnoses and populations from included registries only.
8. Information on primary site, behavior, and histology was coded according to the International Classification of Diseases for
